Tech Stack
-MERN Stack, MongoDB, Express, React, Node.js

Additional Technologies
-HTML, CSS, JavaScript
-Responsive web design
-Render for backend deployment
-Vercel or Netlify for frontend hosting

Project Focus
-Evenly focused full-stack application
-Backend manages authentication, user data, and API communication
-Frontend displays artists, events, and allows users to interact with the app
-Goal is to combine backend data management with a clean user interface

Project Type
-Responsive website
-Accessible on desktop browsers
-Accessible on mobile browsers (Android and iOS)

Project Goal
-Help users discover concerts and live events based on the artists they follow
-Allow users to import or manually add artists they follow
-Display concerts and events near their location
-Allow travel plans to be included(venues/events near your destination)
-Allow users to save events they want to attend
-Provide similar functionality to existing concert discovery apps but support platforms like SoundCloud and Bandcamp

User Demographic
-Music fans who attend concerts regularly
-Users of independent music platforms such as SoundCloud and Bandcamp
-Fans of underground or smaller artists
-Anyone interested in discovering concerts happening near them

Data and APIs
-External APIs will provide concert and artist data
-Bandsintown API will likely be used for concert and event information
-SoundCloud API may be used to retrieve artist information
-Data returned from APIs may include artist names, event dates, venue information, locations, and ticket links

Bandcamp Data Considerations
-Bandcamp does not provide a public API
-Possible solutions include alternative APIs, limited scraping, or allowing users to manually add artists

== Database Schema ==

Users
-Username
-Email
-Password (hashed)
-FollowedArtists
-SavedEvents

Artists
-ArtistName
-PlatformSource
-ExternalAPIid

Events
-Artist
-Venue
-Location
-Date
-TicketLink

Venues
-VenueName
-City
-State
-Location

Saved Events
-UserId
-EventId

Authentication
-User signup
-User login
-Password hashing using bcrypt
-JWT authentication for secure sessions

Potential API Issues
-API rate limits
-Limited access to certain data
-Changes in API structure
-Lack of official API support for Bandcamp

Sensitive Information
-User login credentials will be stored
-Passwords will be hashed using bcrypt
-Authentication sessions will be managed using JWT tokens
-No payment or financial data will be collected

== Core Functionality ==

User Accounts
-User signup
-User login
-Secure authentication

Artist Tracking
-Import artists from supported APIs
-Manually add artists
-Manage followed artists

Concert Discovery
-View upcoming concerts
-Filter concerts by location
-Search artists

Event Management
-Save events
-Remove saved events

Search
-Search artists
-Search concerts

User Flow
-User visits the landing page
-User signs up or logs into their account
-User imports or manually adds artists they follow
-The application retrieves upcoming concerts from external APIs
-The user views concerts happening near them
-The user saves events they want to attend
-The user manages followed artists and saved events

Stretch Goals
-Support additional music platforms
-Include music festivals
-Include smaller venues and local shows
-Notify users when new concerts are announced
-Notify users when followed artists release new music